2
00:00:58.955 --> 00:01:01.860
<i>Who in our generation.</i>

3
00:01:02.061 --> 00:01:05.123
<i>back in the '50s. didn't dance</i>

4
00:01:05.368 --> 00:01:08.416
<i>to this gorgeous. legendary classic</i>

5
00:01:08.881 --> 00:01:10.456
<i>"Samba no Arpège"?</i>

6
00:01:10.668 --> 00:01:13.913
<i>That was Waldir's band.</i>

7
00:01:14.164 --> 00:01:17.664
<i>They played at all
the graduation dances.</i>

8
00:01:17.922 --> 00:01:22.250
<i>And that chorus? Who sings it?
The musicians themselves?</i>

9
00:01:22.485 --> 00:01:26.018
<i>It's the musicians
and your friend here.</i>

10
00:01:26.243 --> 00:01:28.057
<i>How beautiful!</i>

11
00:01:28.339 --> 00:01:32.464
<i>In fact. Waldir himself
also sang the chorus.</i>

12
00:01:32.692 --> 00:01:33.870
<i>Wonderful...</i>

13
00:01:34.156 --> 00:01:37.032
<i>Those who lack life. you see.
don't have the nerve to dance. why?</i>

14
00:01:37.255 --> 00:01:40.396
<i>"Samba no Arpège" is so good.
don't you see?</i>

15
00:01:40.613 --> 00:01:42.144
<i>Let's go! Let's hear it.</i>

16
00:01:42.181 --> 00:01:44.733
<i>"Samba no Arpège".
by Luiz Bandeira and Waldir Calmon.</i>

17
00:02:35.786 --> 00:02:37.830
Our story takes place

18
00:02:37.871 --> 00:02:40.082
in Brazil in 1977.

19
00:02:40.124 --> 00:02:42.793
in very mischievous times...

20
00:03:14.034 --> 00:03:15.120
Hey!

21
00:03:15.870 --> 00:03:17.679
Want me to fill 'er up?

22
00:03:17.956 --> 00:03:20.278
Don't worry about that. that's OK.

23
00:03:20.495 --> 00:03:22.688
- You wanna fill 'er up?
- Well...

24
00:03:25.252 --> 00:03:26.967
Yeah. fill 'er up. but...

25
00:03:28.335 --> 00:03:29.637
What's that about?

26
00:03:29.901 --> 00:03:32.317
Twat was... last Sunday.

27
00:03:32.883 --> 00:03:35.981
An unfortunate man came to steal
a can of oil. with a knife in his hand.

28
00:03:36.186 --> 00:03:38.261
That's when Rivonildo. who works here
at night. grabbed his 12-gauge shotgun

29
00:03:38.467 --> 00:03:42.396
and fired two shots. one on the
chest and the other in the face and...

30
00:03:42.623 --> 00:03:43.722
he never got up again.

31
00:03:44.007 --> 00:03:45.886
Bastard got what he deserved.

32
00:03:46.344 --> 00:03:48.539
Don't worry. you're a customer.

33
00:03:48.758 --> 00:03:50.646
Nothing to do with that. you know?

34
00:03:50.846 --> 00:03:51.858
Okay...

35
00:03:52.178 --> 00:03:54.690
Could you move aside a little so we...

36
00:03:55.056 --> 00:03:56.779
can get closer to the pump.
- You can pull.

37
00:03:57.008 --> 00:03:58.688
- Has he been there since Sunday?
- Yes. yes..

38
00:03:59.150 --> 00:04:01.589
Wait. let me tell you the whole story.

39
00:04:02.031 --> 00:04:04.303
Okay. there you go!

40
00:04:04.578 --> 00:04:07.705
He was from Sunday to Monday.
in the early hours of carnival.

41
00:04:10.897 --> 00:04:12.998
Rivonildo called the owners.

42
00:04:13.573 --> 00:04:15.450
I did too.

43
00:04:17.276 --> 00:04:19.417
but nobody answered.

44
00:04:25.107 --> 00:04:28.105
Rivonildo fled. so he wouldn't
be caught at the crime scene.

45
00:04:28.603 --> 00:04:31.303
He took the opportunity to go out
to the carnival street party...

46
00:04:31.912 --> 00:04:33.814
And I stayed here with this mess.

47
00:04:35.402 --> 00:04:37.204
Open the hood.

48
00:04:44.527 --> 00:04:47.926
If I go away. I'll lose my job.

49
00:04:49.783 --> 00:04:53.623
If I stay here. I'm stuck with rotting flesh.

50
00:04:55.977 --> 00:04:58.410
I'm almost getting used to this shit.

51
00:04:58.634 --> 00:04:59.643
How much?

52
00:05:00.520 --> 00:05:03.142
- Stop at 120. please.
- Right.

53
00:05:03.533 --> 00:05:05.343
You didn't call the police. did you?

54
00:05:05.644 --> 00:05:07.393
Oh. the cops...

55
00:05:07.643 --> 00:05:09.968
We did. they said they'd come
around Ash Wednesday.

56
00:05:11.838 --> 00:05:13.549
because it's too busy during the carnival.

57
00:05:14.143 --> 00:05:15.353
No sign of them so far.

58
00:05:15.675 --> 00:05:18.740
Difficult... It's now Tuesday.
Started stinking yesterday.

59
00:05:19.782 --> 00:05:23.901
- There are some dogs over there!
- Hey dog. come here! Look!

60
00:05:43.369 --> 00:05:45.924
Thanks. man! See you later.

61
00:05:46.275 --> 00:05:47.855
Until finally. at last.

62
00:05:50.659 --> 00:05:51.869
Thank you.

63
00:05:59.543 --> 00:06:03.380
FEDERAL MOTORWAY POLICE

64
00:06:34.336 --> 00:06:37.481
It's been there since Sunday.
You guys took your time!

65
00:06:40.456 --> 00:06:43.065
We didn't even know about that one.

66
00:06:43.215 --> 00:06:45.329
And here I am. begging for help in misery...

67
00:06:45.998 --> 00:06:48.180
- Good day. sir.
- Good day.

68
00:06:49.577 --> 00:06:52.439
License and registration. please.

69
00:06:54.574 --> 00:06:57.594
You didn't come to take care
of the deceased. did you?

70
00:06:57.902 --> 00:07:02.709
No. My colleague asked me to stop
and check out this yellow Volkswagen.

71
00:07:12.355 --> 00:07:15.472
Can you show me
your fire extinguisher. please?

72
00:07:18.411 --> 00:07:21.139
Sir. would you step out of the car.
please?

73
00:07:22.748 --> 00:07:23.861
Why?

74
00:07:30.208 --> 00:07:31.694
You can trust me sir. you know!

75
00:07:32.265 --> 00:07:34.355
Do you really need to get in my car. sir?

76
00:07:34.407 --> 00:07:35.408
It is necessary.

77
00:07:35.792 --> 00:07:37.011
Please. step out.

78
00:07:46.140 --> 00:07:48.035
Wait here. would you?

79
00:08:10.218 --> 00:08:11.754
Fire extinguisher is good.

80
00:08:14.254 --> 00:08:17.729
Yes... it's up to date.

81
00:08:29.993 --> 00:08:31.664
There is nothing toxic in the car.
right?

82
00:08:32.064 --> 00:08:33.779
You don't want to have a smoke.
do you?

83
00:08:35.055 --> 00:08:36.315
No.

84
00:08:39.395 --> 00:08:42.340
- A gun?
- I don't carry a gun.

85
00:08:57.775 --> 00:08:59.658
Drive on. don’t stop.
Go! Go!

86
00:09:15.758 --> 00:09:17.270
Nobody wants to stop.

87
00:09:24.878 --> 00:09:27.241
Isn’t that spare tire too worn out?

88
00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:29.492
That's a good spare.

89
00:09:31.857 --> 00:09:33.285
All right then.

90
00:09:36.959 --> 00:09:38.124
Listen. sir...

91
00:09:43.174 --> 00:09:44.692
Wouldn't you like to...

92
00:09:45.011 --> 00:09:47.590
make a donation to the Police
Force's carnival fund?

93
00:09:49.782 --> 00:09:53.152
- Captain...
- Not captain. I'm a sergeant.

94
00:09:54.023 --> 00:09:57.660
Sergeant. I've been already
traveling for three days.

95
00:09:58.336 --> 00:10:01.441
I just spent all the money
I had left on gas.

96
00:10:04.237 --> 00:10:06.602
If you'd like. there's a...

97
00:10:09.178 --> 00:10:12.234
You can have about three of these.
Cigarettes.

98
00:10:17.106 --> 00:10:18.331
Can I keep them?

99
00:10:18.820 --> 00:10:20.461
Yes. you can keep them.

100
00:10:57.469 --> 00:11:00.238
Get lost! Get the hell out of here!

101
00:11:03.317 --> 00:11:07.158
Bunch of losers. get out. get out!
Beat it! Go! Go!

102
00:11:12.585 --> 00:11:15.462
THE SECRET AGENT

103
00:11:47.774 --> 00:11:50.222
<i>Pernambuco speaking to the world!</i>

104
00:11:50.519 --> 00:11:54.066
<i>Listeners of Jornal do Commercio.
good afternoon!</i>

105
00:12:13.816 --> 00:12:16.109
DRIVEN BY ME
GUIDED BY GOD

106
00:12:16.151 --> 00:12:18.195
<i>It's Carnival Tuesday.</i>
(Mardi Gras)

107
00:12:18.237 --> 00:12:22.242
<i>You're enjoying this heartbreak.
aren't you. my friend?</i>

108
00:12:22.579 --> 00:12:26.978
<i>Having trouble? Then let's enjoy
the Chicago band!</i>

109
00:12:27.219 --> 00:12:28.771
<i>" If you leave me."</i>

110
00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:40.553
WITCHCRAFT IS THE POOR MAN'S TWIST

111
00:13:46.456 --> 00:13:51.669
PART 1
THE BOY'S NIGHTMARE

112
00:13:55.423 --> 00:13:58.092
OCEANOGRAPHY DEPARTMENT

113
00:14:13.050 --> 00:14:14.051
Oh brother!

114
00:14:15.111 --> 00:14:17.209
- Your blessing. dad?
- God bless you.

115
00:14:17.440 --> 00:14:18.441
Dr. Euclides!

116
00:14:18.793 --> 00:14:21.574
Can I have a conversation
with my boys here. is that okay?

117
00:14:21.774 --> 00:14:23.048
Come on! Move aside! Go!

118
00:14:31.627 --> 00:14:33.563
Before going inside...

119
00:14:35.621 --> 00:14:37.536
tell me what's going on.

120
00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:43.074
So. dad. I think it was that Zezinho
from last week.

121
00:14:43.624 --> 00:14:47.107
What's that all about? What a load
of bullshit! Are you crazy. Arlindo?

122
00:14:47.397 --> 00:14:51.558
Would I have pulled dad from the Carnival.
if it were something trivial?

123
00:14:52.951 --> 00:14:54.534
Who's there. taking care of things?

124
00:14:55.140 --> 00:14:57.040
Aristeu. of the Cordeiro precinct.

125
00:14:57.278 --> 00:14:59.338
Damn. what an annoying faggot...

126
00:14:59.648 --> 00:15:00.949
Fernando isn't here?

127
00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:03.135
- Must be at Carnival. right?
- He is!

128
00:15:03.335 --> 00:15:05.598
- Any journalists?
- No.

129
00:15:06.265 --> 00:15:09.168
Only scientists from the university
and some students.

130
00:15:10.920 --> 00:15:13.463
- Is it the right one or the left one?
- I couldn't see it. I was too far away.

131
00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:17.553
But it stinks...

132
00:15:39.867 --> 00:15:42.476
Dr. Euclides. you needn't have come.

133
00:15:42.677 --> 00:15:44.454
I'm really almost done here.

134
00:15:53.812 --> 00:15:57.925
Euclides Cavalcante.
I am Police Chief. At your service.

135
00:16:00.278 --> 00:16:03.175
This appeared on Sunday.
We couldn't waste any time.

136
00:16:03.983 --> 00:16:07.215
- There's no refrigerator here. is there?
- Yes. but it's broken.

137
00:16:07.954 --> 00:16:11.138
As we were working on it.
we found this piece...

138
00:16:11.446 --> 00:16:13.193
I mean. that leg.

139
00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:17.042
I started to remove it.
but I decided better not to.

140
00:16:17.606 --> 00:16:19.070
We called the police.

141
00:16:21.546 --> 00:16:23.568
That's awful...

142
00:16:23.768 --> 00:16:29.771
This shark was found...
where was it killed?

143
00:16:30.060 --> 00:16:33.459
150 meters from the beach.
There... at Candeias.

144
00:16:36.254 --> 00:16:39.632
That leg... is it of a man?

145
00:16:39.907 --> 00:16:44.218
I'd rather not say anything.
That's for a medical examiner to say.

146
00:16:47.207 --> 00:16:49.178
No! Are you going to use
the pocketknife? Calm down!

147
00:16:49.218 --> 00:16:50.684
I'm used to it.

148
00:16:50.884 --> 00:16:52.260
You'll damage the specimen.

149
00:16:52.494 --> 00:16:56.615
I'll remove it myself...
Please wait for me there.

150
00:16:57.531 --> 00:16:58.758
No pocket knives.

151
00:16:59.300 --> 00:17:00.639
My gloves?

152
00:17:05.701 --> 00:17:07.779
Dra. Inês. just a question.

153
00:17:07.991 --> 00:17:09.388
Did they take a picture of the leg?

154
00:17:11.897 --> 00:17:13.583
No. no pictures.

155
00:17:19.575 --> 00:17:22.594
Dr.. is the shark male or female?

156
00:17:30.004 --> 00:17:31.205
Male.

157
00:17:48.617 --> 00:17:49.618
Fuck!

158
00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:52.001
Fuck!

159
00:17:53.122 --> 00:17:55.719
- Mission accomplished.
- Run!

160
00:17:56.922 --> 00:17:59.640
Oh no. he got soaked!

161
00:18:00.821 --> 00:18:01.871
Over here!

162
00:18:03.447 --> 00:18:06.321
- Mrs. Sebastiana?
- Yes. at your service.

163
00:18:06.575 --> 00:18:08.157
- Marcelo?
- It is me.

164
00:18:08.451 --> 00:18:09.472
- All good?
- Very good.

165
00:18:09.743 --> 00:18:11.298
- I need a ride.
- Sure. hop in.

166
00:18:16.276 --> 00:18:18.895
This is Clóvis.
Get on the footboard. kid!

167
00:18:19.109 --> 00:18:20.795
- All good. buddy?
- All.

168
00:18:21.054 --> 00:18:23.410
- Is it safe there?
- Yes. you can go.

169
00:18:24.432 --> 00:18:27.191
The green chickens didn't want to
catch you because of your beard?

170
00:18:28.958 --> 00:18:31.418
- And didn't they rob me today?
- What?

171
00:18:31.656 --> 00:18:33.838
- Oh no. they stole my cigarettes.
- I wouldn't have let them!

172
00:18:34.100 --> 00:18:35.972
But if you need. I have.

173
00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:38.272
I wouldn't let them steal. no way.

174
00:18:38.548 --> 00:18:41.616
- How long have you been smoking?
- Sixty years.

175
00:18:41.840 --> 00:18:43.654
You were born... How old are you?

176
00:18:43.884 --> 00:18:45.890
Seventy-seven. that's what it says
on my birth certificate.

177
00:18:46.077 --> 00:18:47.492
I was born in 1900.

178
00:19:16.758 --> 00:19:19.236
Give him a hand. Clóvis.
take the suitcases out.

179
00:19:19.377 --> 00:19:21.653
- Open the trunk. please.
- It's open.

180
00:19:26.350 --> 00:19:28.480
Hey. welcome.

181
00:19:29.512 --> 00:19:31.840
- Is this the guy?
- That's the one.

182
00:19:32.572 --> 00:19:33.698
Welcome!

183
00:19:33.740 --> 00:19:35.117
OFIRO ASYLUM

184
00:19:37.168 --> 00:19:39.552
Got you some beer.

185
00:19:40.418 --> 00:19:41.773
to welcome you.

186
00:19:45.143 --> 00:19:46.889
Holy Mary...

187
00:19:47.932 --> 00:19:48.941
Haroldo.

188
00:19:50.146 --> 00:19:51.147
Marcelo.

189
00:19:51.655 --> 00:19:53.869
Oh boy...

190
00:19:54.156 --> 00:19:57.811
This party been going since 7 in the
morning. No one's slept for two nights now.

191
00:19:58.019 --> 00:19:59.636
Come on. Mrs. Sebastiana!

192
00:20:00.346 --> 00:20:03.470
- Let's go home. you better rest.
- Indeed.

193
00:20:04.932 --> 00:20:06.529
- Welcome!
- Thanks. thanks.

194
00:20:08.379 --> 00:20:11.782
Look who's here! Teresa Vitória.

195
00:20:12.380 --> 00:20:14.369
This is Marcelo. just arrived.

196
00:20:14.668 --> 00:20:16.618
- All good?
- All good. nice to meet you.

197
00:20:16.847 --> 00:20:17.848
Nice to meet you too.

198
00:20:18.048 --> 00:20:19.179
- Antônio...
- Good afternoon.

199
00:20:19.283 --> 00:20:21.365
The husband of Teresa Vitória.
They're from Angola.

200
00:20:22.310 --> 00:20:25.125
How is it...
How are things over there?

201
00:20:25.466 --> 00:20:27.063
Oh. it's a long story.

202
00:20:28.002 --> 00:20:30.884
We can have a chat and I'll tell you.

203
00:20:32.388 --> 00:20:36.016
Mrs. Sebastiana. everyone is quite
lively today. aren't they?

204
00:20:36.251 --> 00:20:39.327
Leave it to me. I'll take care of it.
I'll ask them to turn the music down.

205
00:20:39.633 --> 00:20:42.711
- My head is about to explode.
- Leave it to me.

206
00:20:42.922 --> 00:20:46.108
- Thank you.
- Get well soon.

207
00:20:46.357 --> 00:20:48.154
- See you later.
- See you later. Nice meeting you.

208
00:20:48.937 --> 00:20:54.046
This is the Ofir building.
I've lived here for 20 years!

209
00:20:54.402 --> 00:20:57.602
And this is my niece Geisa's apartment.

210
00:20:57.845 --> 00:20:59.627
I have prepared everything for you.

211
00:20:59.880 --> 00:21:01.650
You really mean business . you know.

212
00:21:01.931 --> 00:21:04.779
- All nice and tidy.
- This apartment is great. it's beautiful.

213
00:21:05.069 --> 00:21:06.730
Fully furnished.

214
00:21:07.013 --> 00:21:09.825
I asked Clóvis to come and clean it up.

215
00:21:10.314 --> 00:21:13.748
- Excuse me. could I leave it in the bedroom?
- Put it in the bedroom. Clovis.

216
00:21:14.413 --> 00:21:18.035
He did a thorough cleaning. He washed
everything. removed all the dust.

217
00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:20.599
But I wanted more.
Yesterday I came here...

218
00:21:20.894 --> 00:21:25.551
and brought incense.
rue leaves. coarse salt...

219
00:21:25.778 --> 00:21:29.772
- I gave you a thorough cleaning!
- You are absolutely wonderful.

220
00:21:30.508 --> 00:21:32.821
- Make yourself at home. The house is yours.
- Thank you so much.

221
00:21:34.491 --> 00:21:36.395
And you. buddy. are you going to school?

222
00:21:37.288 --> 00:21:38.664
 No. I'm not...

223
00:21:38.710 --> 00:21:41.997
He arrived here last month.
from Rio Formoso.

224
00:21:42.777 --> 00:21:46.073
Hiding. having run away
from his father and uncle.

225
00:21:46.646 --> 00:21:50.491
Because they wanted him to be a man.
the way they wanted him to be!

226
00:21:51.017 --> 00:21:54.458
- Clóvis is a man. right?
- Yes. yes. I am a man.

227
00:21:54.757 --> 00:21:56.909
But not in the way they want.

228
00:21:57.383 --> 00:21:58.890
So. he's helping me out here.

229
00:21:59.258 --> 00:22:03.862
Does everything I ask. water the plants.
picks mangoes. do everything here.

230
00:22:04.155 --> 00:22:08.247
After the soap opera. he goes to sleep.
He will see about his school later.

231
00:22:08.509 --> 00:22:11.284
Right? You have to go to school...

232
00:22:13.324 --> 00:22:15.123
So. there's a cat in the house.

233
00:22:25.777 --> 00:22:28.665
Mrs. Sebastiana. what is this here?

234
00:22:29.742 --> 00:22:31.217
Are you allergic to cats?

235
00:22:32.296 --> 00:22:33.895
No. I do like cats. but...

236
00:22:34.379 --> 00:22:37.721
These kittens were born
in the countryside.

237
00:22:37.990 --> 00:22:41.126
They were going to be put down.
Geisa brought them here.

238
00:22:41.326 --> 00:22:44.052
These are Laiza and Elis.

239
00:22:45.143 --> 00:22:46.670
- Laiza and Elis?
- Yes.

240
00:22:49.065 --> 00:22:51.496
Laiza and Elis...

241
00:22:52.337 --> 00:22:55.877
- Do they come with the apartment?
- More or less...

242
00:22:56.123 --> 00:23:00.176
When Geisa left. she left the cat.
for me to take care of.

243
00:23:00.390 --> 00:23:05.314
They lived upstairs with me. but kept
coming and scratching at Geisa's door.

244
00:23:06.342 --> 00:23:10.892
Then I say. they'll miss Geisa much
and they'll end up ruining the door.

245
00:23:11.123 --> 00:23:13.766
So. I asked Clóvis to make that hole.
It turned out terribly ugly!

246
00:23:14.160 --> 00:23:15.817
I told you it would be ugly.

247
00:23:16.460 --> 00:23:19.277
Yes. you did my son.
It's my fault.

248
00:23:19.877 --> 00:23:21.589
But it turned out ugly.
it really did!

249
00:23:22.012 --> 00:23:23.189
The door ended up ugly.

250
00:23:23.872 --> 00:23:26.701
Now cats and dogs come and go.

251
00:23:29.146 --> 00:23:32.577
Girls. this is Marcelo.
who I told you about.

252
00:23:32.835 --> 00:23:36.971
Marcelo. that's Joana
and the chubby one is Maria.

253
00:23:37.190 --> 00:23:39.263
-Everything alright?
- Excuse me.

254
00:23:40.200 --> 00:23:41.795
They work here. in the building.

255
00:23:42.831 --> 00:23:45.049
Hello. Mrs. Sebastiana.
All good?

256
00:23:45.326 --> 00:23:48.594
This is my new neighbor. Claudia
and her daughter Débora.

257
00:23:48.881 --> 00:23:51.133
- All good?
- All good. Claudia. Nice to meet you.

258
00:23:51.333 --> 00:23:52.372
Nice to meet you.

259
00:23:52.655 --> 00:23:54.031
What's with the girl's head?

260
00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:57.044
- Lice.
- She's infested.

261
00:23:57.638 --> 00:24:00.189
Cláudia is a teacher and a dentist...

262
00:24:00.885 --> 00:24:02.634
Divorced!

263
00:24:03.078 --> 00:24:04.862
She's wonderful...

264
00:24:05.062 --> 00:24:08.658
- She came here to meet you.
- Stop it. Mrs. Sebastiana.

265
00:24:09.597 --> 00:24:12.127
- It'll be alright!
- I was just passing by.

266
00:24:12.364 --> 00:24:14.190
I'll take care of all the work right away.

267
00:24:14.405 --> 00:24:17.111
- Oh madam...
- If that's the case...

268
00:24:19.367 --> 00:24:20.927
- Nice to meet you. Cláudia.
- Likewise.

269
00:24:21.085 --> 00:24:22.920
Welcome to our building.

270
00:24:23.404 --> 00:24:25.942
If you need anything. I live upstairs.

271
00:24:26.387 --> 00:24:28.180
- The floor above?
- Yes.

272
00:24:28.465 --> 00:24:30.202
- Is Clóvis up there?
- He is.

273
00:24:30.456 --> 00:24:32.844
I'll give him some money.
to buy cigarettes.

274
00:24:33.075 --> 00:24:35.127
- Nice to meet you. you know.
- Nice to meet you.

275
00:24:35.386 --> 00:24:37.455
I have now told you everything.

276
00:24:39.951 --> 00:24:45.254
I have a package for you. Here.

277
00:24:46.115 --> 00:24:49.555
You have to be there.
early on Friday morning.

278
00:24:50.196 --> 00:24:52.514
- At five in the morning.
- Thank you.

279
00:24:54.330 --> 00:24:56.267
I'm glad I can help.

280
00:26:22.382 --> 00:26:27.137
<i>I found a house by the sea.</i>

281
00:26:30.015 --> 00:26:34.645
<i>There are coconut trees
and a hammock for us to put up.</i>

282
00:26:39.900 --> 00:26:43.320
<i>And then. my love.</i>

283
00:26:45.197 --> 00:26:49.869
<i>I'll feel love in your arms.</i>

284
00:26:49.910 --> 00:26:52.789
<i>In beautiful splendor.</i>

285
00:26:52.831 --> 00:26:55.000
<i>And then...</i>

286
00:26:55.585 --> 00:26:59.338
<i>We'll walk the road.
no longer just the two of us.</i>

287
00:27:18.901 --> 00:27:21.195
SHARKS (JAWS)

288
00:27:25.815 --> 00:27:27.368
I was drawing that movie poster.

289
00:27:29.701 --> 00:27:31.015
Yes. grandpa.

290
00:27:33.641 --> 00:27:34.642
Yay!

291
00:27:38.748 --> 00:27:41.219
When will I be able to watch it?

292
00:27:42.764 --> 00:27:46.739
- Fernando. it can be watched from age 14.
- Uhum.

293
00:27:47.458 --> 00:27:49.472
Besides. you'll have nightmares. as well.

294
00:27:50.065 --> 00:27:52.666
But I already have nightmares. grandpa.

295
00:28:30.269 --> 00:28:32.798
Now. my peace is finally gone.
isn't it?

296
00:28:33.254 --> 00:28:35.727
Mrs. Lenira. I am going to see my son.

297
00:28:45.509 --> 00:28:47.544
Do you think you should even be here?

298
00:28:48.753 --> 00:28:51.258
I'm going to see Fernando. Mr. Alexandre.
Is he here?

299
00:29:04.258 --> 00:29:05.800
Fernando.

300
00:29:12.360 --> 00:29:16.250
Was there was a leg inside a shark?

301
00:29:17.585 --> 00:29:19.819
What were you afraid of?
A person's leg?

302
00:29:20.055 --> 00:29:21.912
Yes. a human leg.

303
00:29:22.149 --> 00:29:25.297
- Where did you see that? On TV?
- On grandpa's radio.

304
00:29:26.815 --> 00:29:28.984
You can't see things on grandpa's radio.

305
00:29:29.192 --> 00:29:30.388
You can only hear.

306
00:29:30.642 --> 00:29:34.182
We'll have to find that guy.
who lost his leg

307
00:29:34.401 --> 00:29:37.181
and stick it back on.

308
00:29:38.688 --> 00:29:42.976
With a screw or with...

309
00:29:43.176 --> 00:29:46.057
with some glue and some string.
right?

310
00:29:46.308 --> 00:29:48.557
- Or sew it back on.
- Sew...

311
00:29:48.796 --> 00:29:50.688
- Sewing with that thing.
- Yes.

312
00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:58.325
Dad. is mom going to stay
here with us now?

313
00:30:00.371 --> 00:30:04.173
Mom's memory is with us.
right here now. isn't she?

314
00:30:04.572 --> 00:30:09.942
When we think about someone.
it's like having them with us.

315
00:30:14.847 --> 00:30:16.594
But can she come back?

316
00:30:19.633 --> 00:30:24.106
No. son.
Mom got sick and died.

317
00:30:24.507 --> 00:30:26.242
She's not coming back.

318
00:30:26.789 --> 00:30:30.456
Remember when you had the flu.
when you felt better but had a fever?

319
00:30:32.057 --> 00:30:33.673
Yes. I remember.

320
00:30:34.186 --> 00:30:38.488
Pneumonia means
the fever is way. way higher.

321
00:30:39.163 --> 00:30:42.706
Wow... Like 50 degrees?

322
00:30:43.338 --> 00:30:45.183
Like 50 degrees.

323
00:30:46.568 --> 00:30:48.637
So sad. isn't it?

324
00:30:50.567 --> 00:30:53.069
Yes. but we're here. you and me.

325
00:30:54.214 --> 00:30:57.704
And mom is here with us.
her memory is with us.

326
00:30:58.039 --> 00:31:01.414
And I'm not living with you now.
only because I can't.

327
00:31:01.991 --> 00:31:03.919
But that's why I came here.

328
00:31:04.276 --> 00:31:05.277
You see?

329
00:31:05.568 --> 00:31:09.110
So we can live together.
so we can stay together forever.

330
00:31:09.697 --> 00:31:10.698
You and I.

331
00:32:01.992 --> 00:32:07.164
SÃO PAULO STATE

332
00:32:16.169 --> 00:32:18.121
That's always playing the "In the City".

333
00:32:19.099 --> 00:32:20.153
Really?

334
00:32:21.131 --> 00:32:22.257
And what about the women?

335
00:32:25.595 --> 00:32:27.023
Good.

336
00:32:29.313 --> 00:32:31.315
SÉRGIO MOTTA DAM

337
00:32:34.212 --> 00:32:35.318
Oh. there's Oliveira.

338
00:32:37.214 --> 00:32:39.293
- Oliveira!
- Lieutenant.

339
00:32:47.168 --> 00:32:49.904
You know I don't usually
ask questions but...

340
00:32:51.596 --> 00:32:52.992
I got curious.

341
00:32:54.587 --> 00:32:55.957
That old lady over there...

342
00:33:00.450 --> 00:33:02.477
What's it to me if I tell you?

343
00:33:07.146 --> 00:33:08.549
Fuckin' nobody.

344
00:35:15.451 --> 00:35:19.081
Don't fuck around. damn it.

345
00:35:27.009 --> 00:35:29.763
And that woman from yesterday?
I'm curious.

346
00:35:34.964 --> 00:35:38.689
It causes an itch. doesn't it?
That you can't scratch.

347
00:35:52.568 --> 00:35:54.848
Inheritance and envy.

348
00:36:34.003 --> 00:36:35.666
They just got here.

349
00:36:36.202 --> 00:36:37.460
I'm almost done.

350
00:36:38.827 --> 00:36:40.870
GHIROTTI
COMPONENTS OF BRAZIL

351
00:36:52.480 --> 00:36:54.174
This is the person.

352
00:37:02.333 --> 00:37:04.686
Apparently. he's fled to Recife.

353
00:37:04.905 --> 00:37:07.922
I'll find out more and
I'll let you know.

354
00:37:08.301 --> 00:37:11.644
Is he white. indian.
brown or mixed-race?

355
00:37:11.907 --> 00:37:13.300
He's white.

356
00:37:13.947 --> 00:37:15.116
Line of work?

357
00:37:16.440 --> 00:37:19.211
It's in that paper.
The information is in the document.

358
00:37:22.408 --> 00:37:25.107
The one on the right.
With the beard.

359
00:37:25.757 --> 00:37:29.510
Umm... a guy like him...

360
00:37:30.758 --> 00:37:33.253
As you can understand. costs more.

361
00:37:36.626 --> 00:37:39.652
I'll charge you 60.000 cruzeiros.

362
00:37:40.002 --> 00:37:43.370
Plus. travel expenses. accommodation...

363
00:37:46.429 --> 00:37:48.856
I'll pay 40.000.

364
00:37:51.603 --> 00:37:56.527
I want a first-class service.
And I don't want any kind of problems.

365
00:37:56.778 --> 00:38:00.435
Don't contact me again.
Pretend I don't exist.

366
00:38:01.685 --> 00:38:02.728
Figure it out yourself.

367
00:38:05.204 --> 00:38:07.906
With all due respect. Mr. Girotti...

368
00:38:08.145 --> 00:38:09.694
Ghirotti!

369
00:38:10.268 --> 00:38:12.213
Dr. Ghirotti...

370
00:38:12.536 --> 00:38:16.054
We've fought a few battles
together before. isn't it so?

371
00:38:16.347 --> 00:38:20.133
There’s no point in pretending
we are negotiating.

372
00:38:20.415 --> 00:38:22.964
when you know my price is fair.

373
00:38:23.304 --> 00:38:28.107
60.000 cruzeiros.
30.000 now and 30.000 after.

374
00:38:29.190 --> 00:38:31.279
- Are you two always together?
- Always.

375
00:38:31.565 --> 00:38:36.011
That's right.
We'll sign the contract together.

376
00:38:36.611 --> 00:38:40.653
Now. if you don't agree.
I understand and respect it.

377
00:38:46.150 --> 00:38:48.527
These holidays passed in an instant.

378
00:38:50.390 --> 00:38:52.893
He's a despicable man.

379
00:38:55.191 --> 00:38:56.305
I want...

380
00:39:03.804 --> 00:39:05.402
a hole.

381
00:39:07.680 --> 00:39:08.849
A hole?

382
00:39:10.007 --> 00:39:11.224
In his mouth.

383
00:39:12.860 --> 00:39:14.941
Turn into a puppet. you understand?

384
00:39:16.935 --> 00:39:18.517
You can rest assured.

385
00:39:19.931 --> 00:39:23.217
All right. 60.000 it is.

386
00:39:35.935 --> 00:39:38.912
That means you don't have any cavities...

387
00:39:39.884 --> 00:39:42.339
I have dental calculus.

388
00:39:42.813 --> 00:39:45.484
Here! I found a cavity.

389
00:39:46.537 --> 00:39:48.633
Ah. it's huge. isn't it?

390
00:39:48.843 --> 00:39:49.874
Easy.

391
00:39:50.113 --> 00:39:51.581
Marcelo!

392
00:39:55.025 --> 00:39:57.238
Yes. Mrs. Sebastiana?

393
00:39:57.448 --> 00:40:01.009
The groceries are here!
Come have a word with Valdemar.

394
00:40:02.199 --> 00:40:06.449
- Your examination is up.
- It's not over at all. it's not!

395
00:40:25.341 --> 00:40:27.766
I don't feel like kissing. no.

396
00:40:28.591 --> 00:40:31.663
- How so?
- We've kissed a lot already.

397
00:40:39.575 --> 00:40:41.071
It's true.

398
00:40:51.077 --> 00:40:55.308
You know Geisa's story.
Mrs. Sebastiana's niece?

399
00:40:57.547 --> 00:41:00.672
The owner of this bed. of this house.

400
00:41:05.166 --> 00:41:08.863
I was told she went away
and left the house behind.

401
00:41:11.540 --> 00:41:13.103
That's not true.

402
00:41:15.198 --> 00:41:16.776
Her fiancé killed her.

403
00:41:18.889 --> 00:41:22.385
He got angry because she got
a scholarship to study in Germany.

404
00:41:24.228 --> 00:41:26.214
What's this all about. man...

405
00:41:29.029 --> 00:41:32.054
- What a tragedy. isn't it?
- Oh my God...

406
00:41:46.031 --> 00:41:48.046
How come you know this?

407
00:41:49.960 --> 00:41:51.993
Mrs. Sebastiana told me.

408
00:41:53.895 --> 00:41:57.329
I realized she was telling people
a different story.

409
00:42:08.428 --> 00:42:10.687
- Mrs. Sebastiana.
- Hello!

410
00:42:10.899 --> 00:42:14.410
- How are you?
- I'm doing well. I've been worse.

411
00:42:14.651 --> 00:42:17.317
But at 77-year-old. I'm doing great!

412
00:42:22.941 --> 00:42:24.079
Joana!

413
00:42:26.873 --> 00:42:29.961
- Hey. good morning!
- Good morning.

414
00:42:30.812 --> 00:42:33.195
You're ready. darling?
You called. Mrs. Cláudia?

415
00:42:33.474 --> 00:42:35.217
Could you please get my groceries
from downstairs?

416
00:42:35.505 --> 00:42:36.637
Where were you?

417
00:42:37.124 --> 00:42:40.294
Mom helped a man who had a toothache.

418
00:42:45.456 --> 00:42:47.325
Is he giving you a lot of trouble.
ma'am?

419
00:42:47.613 --> 00:42:50.465
I am giving him trouble.
He's in good hands.

420
00:42:50.534 --> 00:42:51.808
I'm crazy about this woman.

421
00:42:52.033 --> 00:42:54.963
- She is our guardian.
- He's well taken care of.

422
00:42:56.073 --> 00:43:00.475
- So. do you come over every week?
- No. it's every Thursday.

423
00:43:00.971 --> 00:43:02.574
My parents have a farm. right?

424
00:43:03.543 --> 00:43:08.043
When I can. I gather the excess.
bring fruit. vegetables...

425
00:43:08.331 --> 00:43:10.347
- So. we don't have to go out there?
- Right.

426
00:43:10.560 --> 00:43:11.982
Maria!

427
00:43:13.329 --> 00:43:15.229
- Mrs. Sebastiana...
- Hello.

428
00:43:15.801 --> 00:43:18.772
- Good morning. Valdemar.
- Good morning. Marcelo.

429
00:43:19.490 --> 00:43:22.147
So. have you been to the refugee market?

430
00:43:23.467 --> 00:43:28.020
- Any mangabas today?
- No. we're out of mangabas.

431
00:43:28.808 --> 00:43:34.751
Let's try to avoid that word. shall we?
We don't use it here.

432
00:43:35.676 --> 00:43:38.205
- "Mangaba"?
- "Refugees".

433
00:43:38.976 --> 00:43:40.387
And what are we then?

434
00:44:08.746 --> 00:44:09.871
<i>Flávia.</i>

435
00:44:11.674 --> 00:44:12.675
Wait a minute.

436
00:44:13.510 --> 00:44:16.713
- I didn't hear you.
- Which date are you listening to?

437
00:44:17.160 --> 00:44:19.975
February 25. 1977.

438
00:44:20.851 --> 00:44:24.414
- Which one are you listening to?
- I'm listening to the '78 tape.

439
00:44:25.158 --> 00:44:28.169
- Of Sebastiana.
- I understood.

440
00:44:33.302 --> 00:44:35.789
<i>The arrangement was...</i>

441
00:44:36.070 --> 00:44:40.913
<i>for him to go to the office
at five in the morning</i>

442
00:44:41.238 --> 00:44:42.987
<i>and look for Anísio.</i>

443
00:44:43.297 --> 00:44:45.176
<i>who was our contact there.
And so he went.</i>

444
00:44:47.095 --> 00:44:50.595
PART 2
IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS INSTITUTE

445
00:44:50.599 --> 00:44:51.840
Wake up. kid.

446
00:44:53.625 --> 00:44:54.943
Keep an eye out.

447
00:44:55.143 --> 00:44:58.454
<i>Human leg found in shark's stomach...</i>

448
00:45:03.614 --> 00:45:05.979
Look at that. man...

449
00:45:06.911 --> 00:45:10.634
"Agronomy student still missing."

450
00:45:11.077 --> 00:45:14.297
Dear Lord. how unlucky can one get...

451
00:45:14.527 --> 00:45:16.862
We couldn't have known.
that he was a good guy. right?

452
00:45:17.141 --> 00:45:19.448
How were we supposed to know
about something like that?

453
00:45:28.764 --> 00:45:30.975
IDENTIFICATION DOCUMENTS INSTITUTE
ROBERTO SANTELMO

454
00:45:39.035 --> 00:45:40.636
Look at that.

455
00:45:40.888 --> 00:45:42.871
I don't know why you're so concerned

456
00:45:43.085 --> 00:45:45.498
about what comes out in the newspaper.

457
00:45:45.699 --> 00:45:49.054
Because there could be
some little communist fuckers

458
00:45:49.450 --> 00:45:52.497
trying to fool us. man.

459
00:45:54.359 --> 00:45:57.040
As long as they don't find the rest.
everything's fine.

460
00:45:57.252 --> 00:45:59.139
One leg won't lead them anywhere.

461
00:45:59.442 --> 00:46:02.746
Now. what about the leg?

462
00:46:03.187 --> 00:46:05.304
It's at the morgue. right?

463
00:46:14.726 --> 00:46:20.709
<i>And introducing our program.
Luiz Cavalcante!</i>

464
00:46:45.328 --> 00:46:48.035
- Marcelo?
- Marcelo. Anísio?

465
00:46:48.598 --> 00:46:50.204
Punctual. you are.

466
00:46:50.456 --> 00:46:52.095
I was told to come early.

467
00:46:52.926 --> 00:46:55.916
We were all told to do the same.
Let's go inside.

468
00:46:59.332 --> 00:47:00.585
- Of pain?
- Yes.

469
00:47:00.844 --> 00:47:02.579
- Bring coffee and water. please.
- OK.

470
00:47:02.931 --> 00:47:04.324
- Easy on the sugar.
- Sure.

471
00:47:04.725 --> 00:47:06.588
You don't have a São Paulo accent.

472
00:47:06.896 --> 00:47:09.386
- I'm from Pernambuco.
- Oh. I see.

473
00:47:11.926 --> 00:47:15.238
But that Pernambuco accent
sounds a bit off. no...

474
00:47:16.284 --> 00:47:19.004
Mr. Geraldo. please stay here.

475
00:47:20.589 --> 00:47:22.170
Good morning. Mrs. Guiomar.

476
00:47:23.035 --> 00:47:25.604
It's like a normal working day.
all right? Sit here.

477
00:47:26.251 --> 00:47:28.316
Anísio. where will I sit?

478
00:47:28.563 --> 00:47:32.939
Let's go over to...
to that last desk over there.

479
00:47:33.433 --> 00:47:35.997
We're here today to support...
To help...

480
00:47:36.253 --> 00:47:38.716
Police Chief Euclides.
whom you saw down there.

481
00:47:40.787 --> 00:47:43.370
The office opens to the public at seven.

482
00:47:44.265 --> 00:47:46.354
That's when you will start working.

483
00:47:46.565 --> 00:47:50.354
We got here at five.
but it only opens at seven?

484
00:47:50.656 --> 00:47:53.664
Yes. You will have some time
to get acquainted.

485
00:47:53.958 --> 00:47:56.713
And most importantly:
to have a quorum.

486
00:47:56.933 --> 00:47:59.670
Oh... have a quorum for what?

487
00:48:27.801 --> 00:48:29.165
<i>Mr. Formiga?</i>

488
00:48:30.373 --> 00:48:32.173
<i>No. Elisângela.</i>

489
00:48:32.847 --> 00:48:35.716
I'm expecting
a parcel of clothes this morning.

490
00:48:35.909 --> 00:48:37.337
Can you keep it by for me?

491
00:48:39.004 --> 00:48:42.006
And tell the boy. as well.
Thank you.

