I got back from postdoc research.

954
01:22:37.878 --> 01:22:39.713
about two years ago.

955
01:22:40.504 --> 01:22:43.884
Now I'm making up
for my research leave.

956
01:22:44.801 --> 01:22:46.428
And I was elected.

957
01:22:47.096 --> 01:22:49.473
Do you ever consider working
in the industry. young man?

958
01:22:50.141 --> 01:22:53.519
An industry makeover would do you
a lot of good.

959
01:22:54.771 --> 01:22:56.939
I enjoy research projects.

960
01:22:56.980 --> 01:22:59.233
Did he say "an industry makeover"?

961
01:22:59.776 --> 01:23:01.986
He said. I needed an industry makeover.

962
01:23:02.028 --> 01:23:03.196
When was that?

963
01:23:04.531 --> 01:23:06.533
That was...

964
01:23:06.575 --> 01:23:08.994
in August 1974.

965
01:23:09.577 --> 01:23:12.538
We introduced him to everyone.

966
01:23:12.580 --> 01:23:14.166
in the department.

967
01:23:14.833 --> 01:23:16.627
Luanda Azevedo was there.

968
01:23:16.668 --> 01:23:18.754
Marcelo Vasconcelos.
Sebastião Peixe...

969
01:23:18.796 --> 01:23:22.341
We introduced everyone.
We gave him a tour.

970
01:23:22.382 --> 01:23:24.761
We showed him our labs.
all our projects...

971
01:23:25.135 --> 01:23:27.472
The electric autonomy project.

972
01:23:27.514 --> 01:23:29.140
the electric car project...

973
01:23:29.182 --> 01:23:31.684
The leather tanning machine.

974
01:23:32.268 --> 01:23:34.854
which was a highlight
of our department.

975
01:23:43.239 --> 01:23:45.887
Let me introduce you to my colleagues.

976
01:23:45.908 --> 01:23:47.887
- Hello guys.
- Hi!

977
01:23:47.911 --> 01:23:49.911
This is Dr. Susan Schaeffer
from the Leeds University.

978
01:23:52.335 --> 01:23:54.335
Sanjay Jasleen. from the École
de Technologie of Quebec.

979
01:23:55.959 --> 01:23:57.459
- Are you English?
- No. not me.

980
01:23:57.483 --> 01:23:59.484
I am. basically. American.

981
01:23:59.508 --> 01:24:00.707
From New York.

982
01:24:00.731 --> 01:24:01.731
But Sanjay...

983
01:24:01.755 --> 01:24:02.855
I am English.

984
01:24:03.180 --> 01:24:04.280
Are you British?

985
01:24:04.304 --> 01:24:05.304
Yes.

986
01:24:05.428 --> 01:24:06.527
Really;

987
01:24:06.551 --> 01:24:08.852
Yes. We studied together in Leeds.

988
01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:11.276
Now. I am living in Quebec.

989
01:24:11.300 --> 01:24:12.400
Yes. of course.

990
01:24:13.224 --> 01:24:15.224
So. here we are. 
He is a good guy.

991
01:24:22.113 --> 01:24:24.949
That was it. The following day.

992
01:24:24.991 --> 01:24:27.119
there was a meeting.

993
01:24:27.660 --> 01:24:30.789
At that meeting. he basically...

994
01:24:31.164 --> 01:24:33.292
shut down the department.

995
01:24:38.756 --> 01:24:40.758
To save time.

996
01:24:40.799 --> 01:24:42.176
I'll go straight to the point.

997
01:24:42.217 --> 01:24:44.304
As far as Eletrobras is concerned.

998
01:24:44.345 --> 01:24:45.971
far away from Pernambuco.

999
01:24:46.680 --> 01:24:49.225
the work you're doing here.

1000
01:24:49.267 --> 01:24:51.770
in my view. should be part of a whole

1001
01:24:52.729 --> 01:24:55.023
I see you all running around
a bit too freely.

1002
01:24:55.064 --> 01:24:57.358
disconnected from us down South.

1003
01:24:58.902 --> 01:25:01.822
I'd like to concentrate in Rio.

1004
01:25:01.864 --> 01:25:04.658
the object of some of your research

1005
01:25:04.700 --> 01:25:06.285
and decision-making.

1006
01:25:06.660 --> 01:25:08.579
Precisely to avoid
that old discussion. that

1007
01:25:08.621 --> 01:25:11.874
things are done one way in the north
and another way in the south.

1008
01:25:12.833 --> 01:25:16.045
I know you people have
this different accent.

1009
01:25:16.421 --> 01:25:19.132
a way of doing things differently.

1010
01:25:19.508 --> 01:25:22.760
Here. even your head of department
has hair.

1011
01:25:23.469 --> 01:25:24.428
Right. Armando?

1012
01:25:27.057 --> 01:25:28.892
Long live differences. right?

1013
01:25:29.643 --> 01:25:32.270
What I'm trying to say is that...

1014
01:25:32.939 --> 01:25:35.315
I was a little surprised by the things
I saw here.

1015
01:25:35.357 --> 01:25:36.483
Sorry...

1016
01:25:36.526 --> 01:25:37.693
Just to...

1017
01:25:37.735 --> 01:25:39.403
Be clear.

1018
01:25:40.028 --> 01:25:44.033
All of the department's projects
are published in the Official Gazette.

1019
01:25:44.075 --> 01:25:45.868
