of the uniform I once wore!

1256
01:46:00.857 --> 01:46:03.427
Let me introduce my stepson. Bobbi.

1257
01:46:03.706 --> 01:46:07.130
Or Abdias. On his birth certificate.
it is Abdias.

1258
01:46:07.857 --> 01:46:12.153
Wow. that's great! Is everything
alright there. Abdias?

1259
01:46:12.984 --> 01:46:14.399
Is the guy a good shot?

1260
01:46:14.695 --> 01:46:16.639
Are you crazy. man?

1261
01:46:17.907 --> 01:46:20.196
This is Sergio. his mother's son.

1262
01:46:20.796 --> 01:46:24.318
That other one there is Arlindo.
an adopted son.

1263
01:46:25.135 --> 01:46:27.028
I prefer "Bobbi". Mr. Euclides.

1264
01:46:27.409 --> 01:46:31.312
Dr. Euclides. I don't work
at the corner store. okay?

1265
01:46:32.087 --> 01:46:37.522
What's with "Bobbi" anyway?
Is that a man's name?

1266
01:46:42.126 --> 01:46:44.855
They were out of men's names that day.
damn it?

1267
01:46:47.464 --> 01:46:50.539
- Dr. Euclides.
- Ah. better.

1268
01:46:50.768 --> 01:46:52.223
This man is tough. son. you see?

1269
01:46:52.470 --> 01:46:55.514
He doesn't like being called "mister".
It gets him worked-up.

1270
01:46:55.806 --> 01:46:58.475
You got that. right?
So. calm down.

1271
01:46:58.917 --> 01:47:01.300
You guys. here on a mission?

1272
01:47:03.449 --> 01:47:04.945
Hey. don't talk like that. son.

1273
01:47:05.165 --> 01:47:08.606
Never mix friendship and work. OK?

1274
01:47:09.761 --> 01:47:14.242
Carnival was lively...
Almost 100 gone.

1275
01:47:14.922 --> 01:47:17.386
I read in the paper about the party.

1276
01:47:17.593 --> 01:47:20.465
There was even a leg.
swallowed by a shark.

1277
01:47:22.264 --> 01:47:23.915
Something for the tourists.

1278
01:47:25.656 --> 01:47:29.273
Speaking of which.
re we going for a "ride"?

1279
01:47:35.606 --> 01:47:36.617
A "ride"?

1280
01:47:38.379 --> 01:47:39.998
We are going for a "ride".

1281
01:47:40.880 --> 01:47:42.819
We are going for a "ride".

1282
01:47:43.844 --> 01:47:45.128
Where are we going?

1283
01:47:45.842 --> 01:47:46.985
Cool it. kid.

1284
01:47:47.236 --> 01:47:50.369
Today we're just tourists. you know?

1285
01:47:50.618 --> 01:47:52.393
we aren't going for no "ride". no.

1286
01:47:56.882 --> 01:47:58.611
But how will it be?

1287
01:47:59.317 --> 01:48:00.983
It's been taken care of.

1288
01:48:03.240 --> 01:48:05.130
It's all been taken care of.

1289
01:48:05.777 --> 01:48:11.695
One is a "157".
The other one is a "157" plus "213".

1290
01:48:13.463 --> 01:48:14.973
They're right back there. look.

1291
01:48:17.008 --> 01:48:18.867
Back there. already?

1292
01:48:19.307 --> 01:48:24.270
"One. five. seven" and "213".
Holy fuck!

1293
01:48:25.299 --> 01:48:26.569
"213" means...?

1294
01:48:27.475 --> 01:48:32.489
It's the commonly known as "rape"!
And "157" is robbery with manslaughter.

1295
01:48:45.292 --> 01:48:47.090
There are only good boys here.

1296
01:50:43.138 --> 01:50:49.133
<i>A local man named Pedro Jorge do
Nascimento. 27-years old. a student.</i>

1297
01:50:49.934 --> 01:50:51.924
<i>resident of Mustardinha.</i>

1298
01:50:52.960 --> 01:50:56.644
<i>was out on an evening walk
in the 13 de Maio Park.</i>

1299
01:50:56.877 --> 01:51:02.042
<i>with a friend named
Alexandrino Borges. 32-years old.</i>

1300
01:51:02.306 --> 01:51:04.828
<i>a dental prosthetist and
resident of Bomba do Hemetério.</i>

1301
01:51:05.243 --> 01:51:10.962
<i>when they were surprised by
a shadow.  that came jumping</i>

1302
01:51:11.408 --> 01:51:13.608
<i>and started kicking them.</i>

1303
01:51:18.060 --> 01:51:20.189
But this is so odd.

1304
01:51:20.685 --> 01:51:23.498
Odd. but we all know what that is.
don't we?

1305
01:51:27.571 --> 01:51:29.657
It's treated as news in the paper!

1306
01:51:30.239 --> 01:51:33.837
Tereza. read the bit about the attack.
It's very good. Read it.

1307
01:51:34.199 --> 01:51:35.749
- But haven't you read it?
- I have. 

1308
01:51:35.958 --> 01:51:38.819
But it's much better to listen
with your Angolan accent. do it!

1309
01:51:40.271 --> 01:51:41.349
Thank you so much.

1310
01:52:10.798 --> 01:52:12.677
Well. look at that!

1311
01:52:13.175 --> 01:52:15.127
Hello. everyone! Wow!

1312
01:52:15.869 --> 01:52:18.638
- Welcome.
- Thank you. my love.

1313
01:52:18.842 --> 01:52:20.703
- All's well?
- All's well. my love.

1314
01:52:20.940 --> 01:52:23.306
Marcelo. it's so good. that you came
for the farewell.

1315
01:52:23.543 --> 01:52:25.258
Mrs. Sebastiana had already told me.

1316
01:52:25.510 --> 01:52:27.796
I was really looking forward to being
here with you guys. Are you well?

1317
01:52:29.755 --> 01:52:32.671
- I'm Geraldo. a friend of Sebastiana's.
- Nice to meet you. all is well?

1318
01:52:33.008 --> 01:52:35.984
"The Hairy Leg"
is all the rage in Casa Amarela.

1319
01:52:36.185 --> 01:52:38.684
It had an air of anarchy.
don't you think?

1320
01:52:38.952 --> 01:52:39.953
Drunkard...

1321
01:52:40.240 --> 01:52:42.779
- Can I make a phone call?
- If it's not long distance. you can.

1322
01:52:43.087 --> 01:52:44.957
Help me with the dishes. Clóvis.

1323
01:52:49.634 --> 01:52:51.083
I don't like Recife.

1324
01:52:55.106 --> 01:52:56.684
I haven't been treated well here.

1325
01:52:56.836 --> 01:53:00.070
Hello. Mrs. Zuleika?
I'm sorry to call you at this hour.

1326
01:53:00.359 --> 01:53:02.117
I really needed to talk to Mr. Alexandre.

1327
01:53:02.319 --> 01:53:03.578
I would like to leave a message.

1328
01:53:04.230 --> 01:53:06.396
I would really like to talk to my son.

1329
01:53:06.647 --> 01:53:09.573
It's a peculiar city. but...

1330
01:53:10.463 --> 01:53:11.464
It's OK.

1331
01:53:12.079 --> 01:53:17.993
"The Hairy Leg" that hops away
would be a big hit in Luanda!

1332
01:53:19.448 --> 01:53:21.316
Thank you. Mrs. Zuleika.
Good night.

1333
01:53:24.667 --> 01:53:27.202
- Is that cachaça?
- It is.

1334
01:53:31.671 --> 01:53:33.661
To your heath. Mr. Marcelo.

1335
01:53:36.028 --> 01:53:38.149
Marcelo is your nickname. right?

1336
01:53:40.223 --> 01:53:41.486
Marcelo...

1337
01:53:44.113 --> 01:53:49.064
My name is Armando. but can call
me Marcelo as well. if you wish.

1338
01:53:57.927 --> 01:54:02.365
I prefer not to reveal my real name.

1339
01:54:03.052 --> 01:54:09.003
"Tereza Victória"... was the name
of a dear aunt of mine.

1340
01:54:09.948 --> 01:54:13.998
Actually. I've always wanted to be
"Tereza Victória".

1341
01:54:14.475 --> 01:54:17.222
- A lovely name.
- I like compound names.

1342
01:54:17.441 --> 01:54:19.942
The names are for your own security.

1343
01:54:22.609 --> 01:54:24.958
It's not easy to be called
by another name.

1344
01:54:25.857 --> 01:54:27.367
It's just a precaution.

1345
01:54:27.620 --> 01:54:30.485
My own name's Sebastiana.
I didn't change it.

1346
01:54:30.822 --> 01:54:32.448
My name's Clóvis.

1347
01:54:34.801 --> 01:54:36.012
Just Clóvis really.

1348
01:54:39.941 --> 01:54:42.129
I wish I had your courage.

1349
01:54:45.173 --> 01:54:47.233
I really do.

1350
01:54:49.009 --> 01:54:51.320
But it's not easy
to live under a death threat.

1351
01:54:56.676 --> 01:54:58.311
I am under a death threat.

1352
01:55:09.599 --> 01:55:11.707
I am as well. under a death threat.

1353
01:55:12.628 --> 01:55:15.414
Let's change this atmosphere.
I will put on some music.

1354
01:55:16.313 --> 01:55:19.427
Look. Mrs. Sebastiana.
I never meant to bring anyone down.

1355
01:55:19.710 --> 01:55:20.711
Give me a hand.

1356
01:55:20.965 --> 01:55:22.086
I said that because...

1357
01:55:22.651 --> 01:55:23.852
I'm alive!

1358
01:55:24.298 --> 01:55:26.961
I'm strong. I have my son.

1359
01:55:29.445 --> 01:55:30.755
I want to live.

1360
01:55:31.863 --> 01:55:32.964
It's just that...

1361
01:55:34.278 --> 01:55:38.800
I found out today.
that I'm under a death threat.

1362
01:55:40.469 --> 01:55:43.193
It was quite a surprise.

1363
01:55:44.388 --> 01:55:47.355
For someone who managed to fight
against both sides in Angola.

1364
01:55:50.522 --> 01:55:52.523
finding refuge here.

1365
01:55:53.411 --> 01:55:54.801
was so good.

1366
01:55:55.986 --> 01:55:58.773
Now António and I are going away.

1367
01:55:59.957 --> 01:56:02.376
On a plane with no Portuguese flag.

1368
01:56:02.577 --> 01:56:03.600
Tereza... 

1369
01:56:03.816 --> 01:56:05.966
- We insisted on that!
- Teresa. you're talking too much.

1370
01:56:07.669 --> 01:56:12.030
Mrs. Sebastiana. you're the best.
Thank you very much.

1371
01:56:13.117 --> 01:56:15.061
Don't mention it.
You're very welcome.

1372
01:56:15.416 --> 01:56:16.889
Tereza. where are you two going?

1373
01:56:17.154 --> 01:56:18.550
That's beside the point. Haroldo.

1374
01:56:19.834 --> 01:56:21.180
But thank you.

1375
01:56:31.517 --> 01:56:34.374
My niece Geisa liked this song very much.

1376
01:56:35.024 --> 01:56:37.529
Better said. she loved it.

1377
01:56:39.577 --> 01:56:40.747
I think it's for me.

1378
01:56:46.768 --> 01:56:48.144
Hello. Mr. Alexandre.

1379
01:56:50.663 --> 01:56:52.028
That's fine. Mr. Alexandre.

1380
01:56:54.535 --> 01:56:55.880
See you later. good night.

1381
01:56:58.687 --> 01:57:01.803
I don't want to see you sad.
I'll show you my little museum.

1382
01:57:02.915 --> 01:57:08.277
Look here... That is my niece.
Geisa. when she was little.

1383
01:57:08.573 --> 01:57:10.267
In this one. she's all grown up.

1384
01:57:10.934 --> 01:57:12.135
Is that you over there. ma'am?

1385
01:57:12.341 --> 01:57:16.228
That's me and my lover
at the time. Andrea.

1386
01:57:16.581 --> 01:57:18.583
That was in Italy. in Sassuolo.

1387
01:57:18.625 --> 01:57:20.377
You lived in Italy. didn't you?

1388
01:57:20.418 --> 01:57:23.622
For seven years. 
From '36 to '42.

1389
01:57:23.950 --> 01:57:26.060
Oh my. you never told me that.

1390
01:57:26.307 --> 01:57:27.639
You never asked me.

1391
01:57:28.020 --> 01:57:30.421
I only came back when the war ended.

1392
01:57:30.674 --> 01:57:32.979
I went to Italy to study music.

1393
01:57:33.976 --> 01:57:37.373
Then I stayed.
things kept getting worse.

1394
01:57:37.612 --> 01:57:39.029
I was unable to come back.

1395
01:57:39.548 --> 01:57:43.034
Over there. I was a communist.
then an anarchist.

1396
01:57:43.234 --> 01:57:45.334
Or the other way around.
I don't remember.

1397
01:57:47.692 --> 01:57:52.746
I saw something there with my own eyes.
that I'm not going to tell you about.

1398
01:57:53.716 --> 01:57:57.045
I'll take it. with me. to my grave.

1399
01:57:58.017 --> 01:58:01.858
I also did three things there.
which I'm not going to tell you.

1400
01:58:02.419 --> 01:58:05.012
But I did it. and I had to.

1401
01:58:05.790 --> 01:58:10.286
To conclude. a toast to you all!

1402
01:58:10.576 --> 01:58:11.577
A toast.

1403
01:58:12.761 --> 01:58:14.784
- To my friend Geraldo.
- Thank you.

1404
01:58:15.062 --> 01:58:18.253
Life has bad things.
but it also has good things.

1405
01:58:18.596 --> 01:58:20.521
To Haroldo. who's not Haroldo.

1406
01:58:20.768 --> 01:58:23.498
A toast to Marcelo. who's Armando.

1407
01:58:24.352 --> 01:58:27.248
To this woman
who is Tereza Victória to me.

1408
01:58:27.849 --> 01:58:30.683
She's off to Sweden with António.

1409
01:58:31.522 --> 01:58:34.834
A toast to Cláudia. who is Cláudia.

1410
01:58:35.807 --> 01:58:37.219
And to Débora.

1411
01:58:37.823 --> 01:58:41.153
who I'm sure will live
in a better Brazil.

1412
01:58:41.369 --> 01:58:44.507
She will grow up in a better Brazil.
with less wickedness.

1413
01:58:44.883 --> 01:58:46.606
Cheers. to everyone.

1414
01:58:46.874 --> 01:58:49.711
Cheers.

1415
01:58:50.770 --> 01:58:53.214
Thank you. Mrs. Sebastiana.

1416
01:59:29.977 --> 01:59:32.345
Look at me. look at me!
I'm here.

1417
01:59:34.145 --> 01:59:36.697
I'm here with you. I'm here.

1418
01:59:40.760 --> 01:59:45.197
PART 3
BLOOD TRANSFUSION

1419
01:59:45.658 --> 01:59:47.144
Oh. damn it...

1420
02:00:08.393 --> 02:00:09.687
Vilmar!

1421
02:00:27.680 --> 02:00:30.409
Dr. Bobbi. Dr. Augusto.

1422
02:00:40.674 --> 02:00:43.101
- Is this the man?
- This is the man.

1423
02:00:46.156 --> 02:00:49.163
Irineu says you're the man.

1424
02:00:50.356 --> 02:00:51.711
I don't know about that.

1425
02:00:52.638 --> 02:00:53.790
Is he up to the job?

1426
02:00:54.471 --> 02:00:55.919
He will manage.

1427
02:00:55.959 --> 02:00:57.843
It's a job right here in Recife.

1428
02:00:59.086 --> 02:01:02.456
Requires great responsibility
and confidence.

1429
02:01:03.253 --> 02:01:04.723
Poor people or rich people?

1430
02:01:04.928 --> 02:01:06.555
I don't know. damn it!

1431
02:01:07.707 --> 02:01:11.244
Looks fancy. but he isn't rich.
right?

1432
02:01:11.526 --> 02:01:13.258
Fancy looking is rich.

1433
02:01:13.961 --> 02:01:15.292
It's more expensive.

1434
02:01:16.434 --> 02:01:18.481
- He carries a gun?
- No...

1435
02:01:19.103 --> 02:01:20.348
That guy's a wimp.

1436
02:01:21.873 --> 02:01:23.095
I'll do it for 4.000.

1437
02:01:23.403 --> 02:01:24.404
Fuck!

1438
02:01:29.436 --> 02:01:31.903
What do you use for the job?

1439
02:01:32.481 --> 02:01:35.538
A medium frame long barrel .38.
A sure shot.

1440
02:01:37.146 --> 02:01:38.772
I'll give you 2.000.

1441
02:01:40.787 --> 02:01:43.204
It's 4.000. I'll do it for 4.000.

1442
02:01:44.779 --> 02:01:46.981
You work in this shithole.

1443
02:01:47.622 --> 02:01:51.424
carrying sugar. doing animal jobs.
to earn peanuts.

1444
02:01:52.737 --> 02:01:54.447
The job is easy. damn it.

1445
02:01:54.911 --> 02:01:58.287
And we have information that
will help you with your job.

1446
02:02:00.624 --> 02:02:02.081
"Animal jobs"...

1447
02:02:02.711 --> 02:02:04.241
I don't like how you talk. no.

1448
02:02:07.173 --> 02:02:08.374
That is our man.

1449
02:02:12.373 --> 02:02:13.582
4.000 it is.

1450
02:02:19.038 --> 02:02:20.736
It's four. then.

1451
02:02:21.740 --> 02:02:23.223
But you're coming now.

1452
02:02:23.468 --> 02:02:26.275
2.000 upfront. now.

1453
02:02:37.755 --> 02:02:39.256
Severino.

1454
02:02:39.352 --> 02:02:41.686
- I'm going out for a bit. okay?
- I'll be back in half an hour.

1455
02:02:41.891 --> 02:02:43.815
- You can leave it to me.
- Take care. you hear!

1456
02:03:28.238 --> 02:03:31.479
If Santa Cruz win today.
I'll buy you a beer. you know?

1457
02:03:33.002 --> 02:03:35.243
- I'm going out and I'll be right back.
- Okay.

1458
02:03:59.877 --> 02:04:01.425
- Hello!
- Good morning.

1459
02:04:01.657 --> 02:04:03.584
- Is Mr. Alexandre here?
- He just left.

1460
02:04:04.033 --> 02:04:05.096
Really?

1461
02:04:07.060 --> 02:04:08.061
Pity.

1462
02:05:38.781 --> 02:05:41.617
HAIRY LEG STEALS
LEG FROM MORGUE

1463
02:05:47.041 --> 02:05:48.476
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1464
02:05:48.941 --> 02:05:50.076
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1465
02:05:50.118 --> 02:05:51.528
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1466
02:05:51.758 --> 02:05:52.928
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1467
02:05:53.118 --> 02:05:54.328
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1468
02:05:54.548 --> 02:05:55.728
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1469
02:05:55.915 --> 02:05:57.020
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1470
02:05:58.619 --> 02:05:59.820
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1471
02:06:00.009 --> 02:06:01.200
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1472
02:06:01.350 --> 02:06:02.480
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1473
02:06:02.650 --> 02:06:03.780
MARIA APARECIDA DOS SANTOS

1474
02:06:03.849 --> 02:06:05.000
Maria Aparecida dos Santos

1475
02:06:05.099 --> 02:06:06.250
MARIA APARECIDA DOS SANTOS

1476
02:06:08.201 --> 02:06:10.061
Maria Augusta?

1477
02:06:10.707 --> 02:06:12.781
- Maria Aparecida?
- Maria Aparecida.

1478
02:06:13.636 --> 02:06:15.108
Quite a few of them.

1479
02:06:17.382 --> 02:06:18.479
Is it your mother?

1480
02:06:24.153 --> 02:06:26.311
You're really committed to this. huh?

1481
02:06:28.785 --> 02:06:32.191
My mother died
and I'd like to have a document of her.

1482
02:06:33.169 --> 02:06:34.678
Even if only one.

1483
02:06:37.412 --> 02:06:40.829
And I know
her ID card was issued here.

1484
02:06:41.805 --> 02:06:44.443
I desperately want to find that file now.

1485
02:06:46.274 --> 02:06:48.312
I hope you'll find it.

1486
02:07:21.359 --> 02:07:22.741
- Morning.
- Morning.

1487
02:07:45.612 --> 02:07:47.211
- Morning. boss.
- Morning.

1488
02:07:47.411 --> 02:07:49.729
Is this where they issue ID cards?

1489
02:07:49.998 --> 02:07:51.019
Yes. sir.

1490
02:08:09.396 --> 02:08:12.180
Brenda Oliveira da Mata.

1491
02:08:12.401 --> 02:08:13.887
I came to speak with an employee.

1492
02:08:14.116 --> 02:08:15.919
- Maria Eugênia Cox.
- Armando!

1493
02:08:21.791 --> 02:08:23.884
You can let him in.

1494
02:08:39.480 --> 02:08:41.611
- Is everything alright?
- I called you Armando...

1495
02:08:41.879 --> 02:08:44.984
- Is Fernando alright?
- He's fine. He asked me to give you this.

1496
02:08:45.945 --> 02:08:47.294
He kept bothering me.

1497
02:08:47.554 --> 02:08:49.963
I had to swear that I would bring
it to you this morning.

1498
02:08:59.234 --> 02:09:00.751
Turn it over.

1499
02:09:07.418 --> 02:09:10.463
<i>Dad. grandpa and grandma
are very nice.</i>

1500
02:09:12.771 --> 02:09:15.274
<i>but I want to live with you.</i>

1501
02:09:17.761 --> 02:09:19.591
<i>Mariana da Rocha Pinheiro</i>

1502
02:09:20.162 --> 02:09:26.097
<i>I think I'm starting to forget
about mom.</i>

1503
02:09:27.314 --> 02:09:28.714
<i>Come back quickly.</i>

1504
02:09:29.988 --> 02:09:31.109
<i>Fernando.</i>

1505
02:09:31.770 --> 02:09:33.531
<i>Eduardo Lopes da Paz</i>

1506
02:09:37.530 --> 02:09:40.903
<i>Célia Maria Tavares Correia</i>

1507
02:09:48.513 --> 02:09:50.323
You're taking my grandson away.

1508
02:09:52.229 --> 02:09:53.841
I'm taking my son.

1509
02:09:56.974 --> 02:10:00.070
You really have to take him.
You should take him.

1510
02:10:01.316 --> 02:10:02.458
I need to go.

1511
02:10:03.448 --> 02:10:05.290
Did you find your mother's document?

1512
02:10:05.490 --> 02:10:06.491
No.

1513
02:10:09.010 --> 02:10:11.600
<i>Gabriel dos Anjos Barros</i>

1514
02:10:16.143 --> 02:10:18.566
<i>Cláudia Andrade Lima Melo.</i>

1515
02:10:22.872 --> 02:10:24.910
<i>Amélia Bastos Silva?</i>

1516
02:10:26.376 --> 02:10:29.454
<i>Mariana da Rocha Pinheiro</i>

1517
02:10:31.733 --> 02:10:32.761
<i>Mariana?</i>

1518
02:10:34.551 --> 02:10:37.062
<i>Kauã Barros Campos</i>

1519
02:10:39.659 --> 02:10:42.580
<i>Inaê Leão Marinho</i>

1520
02:10:46.923 --> 02:10:50.177
<i>Next. Kauã Barros Campos?</i>

1521
02:10:52.006 --> 02:10:54.756
<i>Amélia Vasco Silva?</i>

1522
02:10:55.287 --> 02:10:57.677
<i>Mariana da Rocha Pinheiro</i>

1523
02:10:58.079 --> 02:11:01.577
<i>Mariana da Rocha Pinheiro?</i>

1524
02:11:03.172 --> 02:11:07.571
<i>Edivaldo Cordeiro Monteiro Filho</i>

1525
02:11:10.498 --> 02:11:13.777
<i>Claudia Andrade Lima Melo</i>

1526
02:11:18.933 --> 02:11:22.617
<i>Demóstenes Guerra Ferreira</i>

1527
02:11:24.590 --> 02:11:26.801
<i>Natália de Oliveira Silva?</i>

1528
02:11:27.001 --> 02:11:28.091
Girl.

1529
02:11:28.591 --> 02:11:30.067
- Right?
- Is that Armando?

1530
02:11:38.923 --> 02:11:41.773
No. His name is Marcelo.

1531
02:11:42.323 --> 02:11:43.324
Armando!

1532
02:11:54.884 --> 02:11:55.966
Armando!

1533
02:11:59.098 --> 02:12:01.169
His name's not Armando.

1534
02:12:49.996 --> 02:12:53.991
Take a couple of big guys.
and go give him a scare.

1535
02:12:54.260 --> 02:12:56.190
We only have two patrol cars.

1536
02:12:56.409 --> 02:12:59.045
Excuse me. Dr. Euclides.
excuse me. how are you?

1537
02:12:59.245 --> 02:13:00.746
Tell me. Tell me. Marcelo.

1538
02:13:01.361 --> 02:13:04.780
- I wanted to talk to you.
- Go ahead.

1539
02:13:05.129 --> 02:13:07.953
Dr. Euclides. you know that
I don't carry a weapon.

1540
02:13:09.151 --> 02:13:11.338
We're very exposed down there.

1541
02:13:12.492 --> 02:13:15.177
There is a citizen. down there.
who showed up.

1542
02:13:15.972 --> 02:13:17.585
was disrespective to the girls.

1543
02:13:17.789 --> 02:13:18.790
Oh. my...

1544
02:13:19.042 --> 02:13:20.229
He threatened me!

1545
02:13:21.926 --> 02:13:23.526
And he's over there looking for trouble.

1546
02:13:23.611 --> 02:13:25.113
So. I thought it best to speak with you.

1547
02:13:26.367 --> 02:13:30.878
You have to walk around armed. my man.
Commands respect. damn it!

1548
02:13:33.611 --> 02:13:35.074
Stretch your arm out.

1549
02:13:36.221 --> 02:13:37.222
Stretch your...

1550
02:13:37.576 --> 02:13:40.327
The hand. he wants to see your hand.
Stretch it out.

1551
02:13:44.630 --> 02:13:47.766
He is nervous.

1552
02:13:49.982 --> 02:13:51.446
Did you mess with his wife?

1553
02:13:51.841 --> 02:13:53.540
No! I don't know that guy.

1554
02:13:53.884 --> 02:13:55.285
He's down there now.

1555
02:13:56.327 --> 02:13:57.702
Dr. Euclides.

1556
02:14:00.019 --> 02:14:03.434
I wouldn't have come here.
asking for your help.

1557
02:14:04.076 --> 02:14:06.545
if I didn't think that
it is a dangerous situation.

1558
02:14:08.673 --> 02:14:11.444
Arlindo. go and check it out.

1559
02:14:12.016 --> 02:14:14.024
Leave it to me.
I was itching to do it myself.

1560
02:14:14.266 --> 02:14:15.354
Thanks you.

1561
02:14:17.732 --> 02:14:20.297
Marcão. let's go down
and sort out a problem.

1562
02:14:20.493 --> 02:14:22.740
- Now?
- It'll be quick. We'll be right back.

1563
02:14:29.469 --> 02:14:31.054
SWINDLERS AND CON ARTISTS
SSPPE

1564
02:14:34.871 --> 02:14:37.769
<i>Lieutenant! Hey. Lieutenant!</i>

1565
02:14:38.645 --> 02:14:39.729
<i>Telephone!</i>

1566
02:14:52.061 --> 02:14:53.114
Hello.

1567
02:14:54.040 --> 02:14:57.842
<i>Mr. Augusto. it's Vilmar.
I found the man.</i>

1568
02:14:58.241 --> 02:14:59.717
Where did you find him?

1569
02:15:00.978 --> 02:15:04.481
At the office that issues ID cards.

1570
02:15:05.206 --> 02:15:08.962
- Are you sure it's him?
<i>-I am sure.</i>

1571
02:15:09.247 --> 02:15:10.987
I took a quick look and everything.

1572
02:15:22.070 --> 02:15:24.588
<i>Claudio Ferraz Gomes da Silva</i>

1573
02:15:25.542 --> 02:15:26.572
Is he to be taken out?

1574
02:15:29.600 --> 02:15:31.719
Is Bobbi there with you?

1575
02:15:32.299 --> 02:15:34.772
<i>No. he stayed at the cinema.</i>

1576
02:15:35.789 --> 02:15:36.790
Better.

1577
02:15:39.209 --> 02:15:40.501
Take him out.

1578
02:15:41.428 --> 02:15:42.493
You can count on to me.

1579
02:15:42.736 --> 02:15:43.989
There he is. at the payphone.

1580
02:15:44.203 --> 02:15:46.927
<i>Célia Maria Tavares Correia</i>

1581
02:15:48.290 --> 02:15:50.108
That guy with the red cap?

1582
02:15:50.308 --> 02:15:51.377
Let's go. Marcão.

1583
02:15:59.417 --> 02:16:01.929
I have the rest of your money.
here with me.

1584
02:16:03.210 --> 02:16:06.915
Hey there. big guy!
Are you bothering one of our friends?

1585
02:16:08.667 --> 02:16:10.338
Show us your ID card!

1586
02:16:13.375 --> 02:16:15.189
Man. I know who that guy is.

1587
02:16:16.576 --> 02:16:18.270
Of all days. I forgot my ID today.

1588
02:16:18.782 --> 02:16:19.783
No!

1589
02:16:23.053 --> 02:16:24.054
It's a gunshot!

1590
02:17:13.373 --> 02:17:15.398
There was a shooting there.
What a disaster!

1591
02:17:18.625 --> 02:17:20.128
Son of a bitch!

1592
02:17:30.295 --> 02:17:35.852
<i>Don't do tomorrow. what you
can do the day after tomorrow!</i>

1593
02:17:36.566 --> 02:17:42.479
<i>Long live procrastination!
Long live collective idleness!</i>

1594
02:17:49.124 --> 02:17:51.077
Did you see a man with a red cap?

1595
02:17:51.277 --> 02:17:52.278
That way?

1596
02:18:09.410 --> 02:18:12.786
Paid love is cheaper than free love!

1597
02:18:20.591 --> 02:18:22.896
Prevision and that thing called foresight!

1598
02:18:24.129 --> 02:18:27.780
<i>Desire keeps on growing!</i>

1599
02:18:29.191 --> 02:18:32.462
<i>The future. glory. are of no value!</i>

1600
02:18:33.238 --> 02:18:36.586
<i>No matter the glory. the horizon line...</i>

1601
02:18:37.088 --> 02:18:39.706
What I see is an alley!

1602
02:18:40.195 --> 02:18:43.134
<i>Oh. the book. oh. the book. oh. the book!
A book to give away!</i>

1603
02:18:43.538 --> 02:18:46.636
Let's go! Go. damn it. go!
Let's go!

1604
02:18:48.455 --> 02:18:53.494
Damn it! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!
Help! Help! Help us. please!

1605
02:19:02.723 --> 02:19:03.764
Where's Arlindo?

1606
02:19:06.054 --> 02:19:08.218
- Did you see what happened?
- I saw.

1607
02:19:22.384 --> 02:19:26.367
<i>Love is rebellious!
It can't be kept in a cage.</i>

1608
02:19:27.046 --> 02:19:29.040
<i>Needs to be free
And takes no charity!</i>

1609
02:19:32.846 --> 02:19:37.472
<i>So. take care of what's yours!
Before it's gone.</i>

1610
02:19:38.219 --> 02:19:40.488
<i>Never to return!</i>

1611
02:19:41.398 --> 02:19:42.439
<i>I am a plant.</i>

1612
02:19:42.972 --> 02:19:44.265
<i>I have roots</i>

1613
02:19:45.492 --> 02:19:47.186
<i>I am a wild animal!</i>

1614
02:19:48.835 --> 02:19:51.349
I walk freely and happily.
following my destiny.

1615
02:19:51.564 --> 02:19:53.731
<i>Saving up my money. which
will arrive another day!</i>

1616
02:20:00.332 --> 02:20:03.955
<i>My path must be clear!
I don't accept charity!</i>

1617
02:20:04.267 --> 02:20:07.886
<i>So. take care of yours.
before it's gone!</i>

1618
02:20:13.258 --> 02:20:15.674
Marcelo.
these files can't leave this room.

1619
02:20:16.919 --> 02:20:19.881
All lines are busy
because of what happened.

1620
02:20:25.262 --> 02:20:28.599
Tell me.
your name's not Marcelo. is it?

1621
02:21:48.434 --> 02:21:50.477
""Animal jobs"...

1622
02:22:00.863 --> 02:22:01.990
Elza.

1623
02:22:04.200 --> 02:22:06.244
I need the passports now.

1624
02:22:07.746 --> 02:22:08.830
Elza...

1625
02:22:09.581 --> 02:22:11.333
My time in Recife is over.

1626
02:22:29.852 --> 02:22:32.647
Stand back!
Clear off!

1627
02:22:55.296 --> 02:22:57.840
CARNIVAL DEATH TOLL: 91

1628
02:22:59.553 --> 02:23:05.264
SOUTHERN TOURIST SHOT
AT BARBER SHOP

1629
02:23:08.396 --> 02:23:10.940
Motive may have been revenge.

1630
02:23:21.116 --> 02:23:21.908
Dani.

1631
02:23:25.870 --> 02:23:26.579
Dani.

1632
02:23:29.165 --> 02:23:30.250
Yes?

1633
02:23:30.292 --> 02:23:31.376
Tell me.

1634
02:23:31.418 --> 02:23:35.589
Did you try to find out
what happened to these people?

1635
02:23:36.673 --> 02:23:39.176
You know I'm kind of anxious.

1636
02:23:39.218 --> 02:23:43.931
I tried Googling them.
but there's nothing there.

1637
02:23:43.973 --> 02:23:45.432
They're all pre-Google.

1638
02:23:45.808 --> 02:23:47.518
We need to scan the newspapers.

1639
02:23:48.853 --> 02:23:50.981
Yes. but that's more work.

1640
02:23:51.023 --> 02:23:53.984
I'm listening to Anísio.
who tried to help Armando.

1641
02:23:54.026 --> 02:23:54.985
you know?

1642
02:23:55.027 --> 02:23:57.361
You went back to the Armando case?

1643
02:23:57.404 --> 02:24:00.157
You were a bit shaken by it.
weren't you?

1644
02:24:00.824 --> 02:24:03.368
Yes. I needed a break from it.

1645
02:24:07.080 --> 02:24:08.248
Well...

1646
02:24:08.999 --> 02:24:12.711
I don't know why.
but this guy's story got to me.

1647
02:24:14.297 --> 02:24:17.216
Probably because
my family's from Pernambuco.

1648
02:24:17.258 --> 02:24:20.345
My grandfather.
who was practically my father.

1649
02:24:23.473 --> 02:24:27.936
I liked hearing Armando's voice
on my headphones.

1650
02:24:30.939 --> 02:24:33.107
He had a good voice.

1651
02:24:46.206 --> 02:24:49.834
MURDERED RESEARCHER
WAS ACCUSED OF CORRUPTION

1652
02:24:50.543 --> 02:24:51.753
Shall I take him?

1653
02:25:08.104 --> 02:25:11.315
Armando Solimões. 43. shot dead...

1654
02:25:11.357 --> 02:25:13.818
crime being treated as a hit job.

1655
02:25:22.911 --> 02:25:24.204
Say dad.

1656
02:25:36.676 --> 02:25:38.303
Thank you. bye.

1657
02:25:51.400 --> 02:25:52.985
- Good evening.
- Good evening.

1658
02:25:53.027 --> 02:25:56.071
I'd like to see
Dr. Fernando de Melo Solimões.

1659
02:25:56.113 --> 02:25:57.698
He's expecting me.

1660
02:25:57.740 --> 02:25:59.408
Dr. Fernando.

1661
02:25:59.450 --> 02:26:01.327
- Flávia. right?
- Exactly.

1662
02:26:01.368 --> 02:26:03.038
You're donating?

1663
02:26:05.205 --> 02:26:06.415
I am.

1664
02:26:06.457 --> 02:26:07.917
How much do you weigh?

1665
02:26:07.959 --> 02:26:10.295
52 kilos.

1666
02:26:25.685 --> 02:26:26.896
Flávia?

1667
02:26:28.689 --> 02:26:30.191
Dr. Fernando.

1668
02:26:30.858 --> 02:26:32.610
Very nice to meet you.

1669
02:26:33.110 --> 02:26:34.070
How are you?

1670
02:26:34.112 --> 02:26:37.406
I was joking when I said
I'd only see you if you gave blood.

1671
02:26:38.532 --> 02:26:40.409
It's a good thing. though.

1672
02:26:40.451 --> 02:26:42.829
First time I've given blood.

1673
02:26:43.245 --> 02:26:45.791
You're in good hands.
Right. Rosa?

1674
02:26:45.831 --> 02:26:47.042
Everything is fine.

1675
02:26:47.668 --> 02:26:49.461
Can I see my blood?

1676
02:26:54.384 --> 02:26:55.634
You from Minas Gerais?

1677
02:26:56.969 --> 02:27:00.223
Yes. but I've lived in São Paulo
for a few years.

1678
02:27:00.264 --> 02:27:03.893
I wasn't really into the idea.
at first.

1679
02:27:03.935 --> 02:27:06.396
but I'm happy I've done this.

1680
02:27:08.065 --> 02:27:10.066
- Can I get this?
- Yes. please.

1681
02:27:10.108 --> 02:27:11.359
Thanks. Rosa.

1682
02:27:11.401 --> 02:27:12.485
Thank you. Rosa.

1683
02:27:12.527 --> 02:27:16.323
It's snacks now.
I'll get her a chocolate milk.

1684
02:27:19.618 --> 02:27:22.162
I know your father spent some time.

1685
02:27:22.204 --> 02:27:25.249
searching for an identity record
of his mother.

1686
02:27:25.290 --> 02:27:27.084
here in Recife. didn't he?

1687
02:27:27.126 --> 02:27:28.752
It's on the tapes.

1688
02:27:28.794 --> 02:27:30.713
You see. I don't know...

1689
02:27:30.754 --> 02:27:32.506
I didn't know that.

1690
02:27:32.924 --> 02:27:35.384
About my grandmother
on my father's side.

1691
02:27:35.426 --> 02:27:37.345
all I know is her name.

1692
02:27:37.387 --> 02:27:39.556
"Maria Aparecida dos Santos"

1693
02:27:39.597 --> 02:27:41.204
known as "Índia".

1694
02:27:41.266 --> 02:27:42.977
That's all I know.

1695
02:27:43.811 --> 02:27:48.315
Do you have any papers
of your grandmother?

1696
02:27:48.357 --> 02:27:50.192
Nothing. I never saw her.

1697
02:27:50.234 --> 02:27:51.901
No pictures. nothing.

1698
02:27:51.943 --> 02:27:53.279
No records whatsoever.

1699
02:27:55.531 --> 02:27:57.700
My grandfather on my father's side.

1700
02:27:57.742 --> 02:28:02.496
impregnated the daughter
of the family's housemaid in Bonito.

1701
02:28:02.538 --> 02:28:04.291
here in Pernambuco.

1702
02:28:05.083 --> 02:28:07.293
My grandfather was 17.

1703
02:28:07.335 --> 02:28:09.921
and my grandmother was 14. a child.

1704
02:28:09.963 --> 02:28:11.632
She was like...

1705
02:28:13.967 --> 02:28:17.095
She did all the housework.

1706
02:28:17.137 --> 02:28:19.766
She was a kind of servant...

1707
02:28:19.807 --> 02:28:21.058
Like...

1708
02:28:21.643 --> 02:28:23.436
a slave...
or an enslaved person.

1709
02:28:23.478 --> 02:28:25.021
I don't know...

1710
02:28:25.563 --> 02:28:27.523
She really was enslaved.

1711
02:28:29.442 --> 02:28:33.946
And my grandmother was known as...

1712
02:28:33.988 --> 02:28:37.284
Everyone called her "Índia".
just "Índia".

1713
02:28:38.077 --> 02:28:40.411
And my father. her son...

1714
02:28:41.205 --> 02:28:44.541
Everyone said he was
a "handsome" boy.

1715
02:28:45.542 --> 02:28:47.795
So she was "Índia".

1716
02:28:48.087 --> 02:28:50.547
and my father was "Handsome".

1717
02:28:52.174 --> 02:28:53.468
You see?

1718
02:28:55.135 --> 02:28:56.680
It's not easy.

1719
02:28:56.971 --> 02:29:01.559
I find it so hard
to speak about this...

1720
02:29:01.601 --> 02:29:03.979
I'm doing it because you insisted.

1721
02:29:05.605 --> 02:29:09.235
You're really something else.
you sent emails. you called...

1722
02:29:09.276 --> 02:29:12.404
But it's hard for me
to speak about this.

1723
02:29:13.906 --> 02:29:15.198
But...

1724
02:29:15.240 --> 02:29:17.410
What about your father Armando?

1725
02:29:17.451 --> 02:29:18.828
My father Armando

1726
02:29:18.869 --> 02:29:21.247
was born of that relationship

1727
02:29:21.288 --> 02:29:25.960
between a 17-year-old boy
and a 14-year-old girl.

1728
02:29:26.503 --> 02:29:27.587
And...

1729
02:29:27.629 --> 02:29:31.591
The wealthy side of the family...
"Wealthy" so to speak...

1730
02:29:31.633 --> 02:29:34.177
That is. my grandfather's family.

1731
02:29:34.803 --> 02:29:36.763
They took my father to raise him.

1732
02:29:36.805 --> 02:29:40.058
and his mother couldn't do anything.
she was a child.

1733
02:29:43.562 --> 02:29:46.858
Listen. here's the thing.

1734
02:29:47.274 --> 02:29:50.737
I work for a private university.

1735
02:29:51.029 --> 02:29:54.574
that paid me to transcribe the tapes.

1736
02:29:54.615 --> 02:29:57.118
they got from that archive.

1737
02:29:57.410 --> 02:30:01.831
And now they want the tapes back.

1738
02:30:01.873 --> 02:30:06.128
they feel there's
sensitive information on them.

1739
02:30:06.627 --> 02:30:09.548
So they asked for all the tapes back.

1740
02:30:10.425 --> 02:30:12.551
But that doesn't really matter.

1741
02:30:12.593 --> 02:30:15.972
because I made copies
of all the recordings.

1742
02:30:17.932 --> 02:30:19.809
I said you're something else.
didn't I?

1743
02:30:21.102 --> 02:30:25.148
But also the reason I came is.

1744
02:30:25.190 --> 02:30:28.485
I appreciated hearing
your father's testimony.

1745
02:30:29.194 --> 02:30:31.572
Hearing people talk about him.

1746
02:30:31.614 --> 02:30:33.324
Flávia...

1747
02:30:34.157 --> 02:30:37.536
How did those recordings reach you?

1748
02:30:38.954 --> 02:30:41.374
Through the daughter of Sara Guebert.

1749
02:30:41.415 --> 02:30:44.585
whom your father knew as "Elza"

1750
02:30:44.627 --> 02:30:46.921
when he was under persecution.

1751
02:30:55.555 --> 02:30:58.475
Flávia. I won't go into that.

1752
02:30:59.393 --> 02:31:00.435
Okay?

1753
02:31:03.021 --> 02:31:04.439
That's all right.

1754
02:31:05.525 --> 02:31:07.192
In fact...

1755
02:31:09.570 --> 02:31:11.155
I've brought this.

1756
02:31:11.531 --> 02:31:13.825
with all the recordings I copied.

1757
02:31:14.450 --> 02:31:15.952
Everything I got.

1758
02:31:16.494 --> 02:31:18.205
is in here.

1759
02:31:18.746 --> 02:31:20.707
Your father's voice is here.

1760
02:31:21.208 --> 02:31:23.501
and people talking about him.

1761
02:31:24.585 --> 02:31:25.713
It's yours.

1762
02:31:25.754 --> 02:31:29.425
You can keep it
and do whatever you like with it.

1763
02:31:41.563 --> 02:31:44.065
You know. my grandfather Alexandre...

1764
02:31:45.607 --> 02:31:47.027
who brought me up

1765
02:31:48.778 --> 02:31:51.072
and who I consider to be my father...

1766
02:31:53.450 --> 02:31:55.161
He told me that...

1767
02:31:55.202 --> 02:31:57.537
He was always telling this story.

1768
02:31:57.579 --> 02:31:59.874
When my father...

1769
02:32:00.750 --> 02:32:03.878
The day my father died.
I was showered and ready.

1770
02:32:03.919 --> 02:32:07.506
I'd put on my favorite clothes
and I stood there.

1771
02:32:07.965 --> 02:32:10.926
outside the house.
waiting for him.

1772
02:32:10.968 --> 02:32:14.431
The plan was
he'd come to pick me up.

1773
02:32:15.307 --> 02:32:19.602
I honestly don't remember that.

1774
02:32:20.604 --> 02:32:23.774
Like. someone tells you something
and you create a memory.

1775
02:32:23.815 --> 02:32:27.028
But I don't know if I remember that day.

1776
02:32:29.488 --> 02:32:33.576
I am talking to you about him.
but I don't...

1777
02:32:33.951 --> 02:32:36.829
The truth is. I don't remember him.

1778
02:32:39.248 --> 02:32:41.042
The truth is.

1779
02:32:41.584 --> 02:32:45.129
you remember my father.
more than I do.

1780
02:33:02.356 --> 02:33:04.316
I don't think I helped you much.

1781
02:33:04.358 --> 02:33:05.735
It's all right.

1782
02:33:05.777 --> 02:33:07.904
It was great to meet you.

1783
02:33:07.946 --> 02:33:11.241
This trip to Recife is also
an opportunity for me.

1784
02:33:11.282 --> 02:33:15.912
to meet some relatives.
I only know through the phone.

1785
02:33:15.954 --> 02:33:17.707
You have family here?

1786
02:33:17.747 --> 02:33:19.542
My grandfather is from here.

1787
02:33:19.583 --> 02:33:22.253
He worked for a family

1788
02:33:22.294 --> 02:33:25.089
not far from here. on Chora
Menino ("Cry. Boy") Square.

1789
02:33:26.716 --> 02:33:31.053
I love that. "Chora Menino".
Great name for a square.

1790
02:33:31.679 --> 02:33:35.851
I've heard about this place
since I was little.

1791
02:33:35.892 --> 02:33:38.394
Quite a coincidence.
me ending up here.

1792
02:33:40.187 --> 02:33:42.107
You want a coincidence?

1793
02:33:42.982 --> 02:33:44.609
When I was little.

1794
02:33:45.277 --> 02:33:47.739
I really wanted
to see that movie "Jaws".

1795
02:33:47.780 --> 02:33:49.197
- I know it.
- You do?

1796
02:33:50.032 --> 02:33:52.327
My grandfather would not let me.

1797
02:33:52.368 --> 02:33:54.454
the poster alone scared me.

1798
02:33:54.495 --> 02:33:57.081
the shark with that huge mouth.

1799
02:33:57.123 --> 02:34:01.252
He was a projectionist
at the São Luiz cinema.

1800
02:34:01.753 --> 02:34:04.005
One day. he took me to see it.

1801
02:34:04.047 --> 02:34:05.381
Out of the blue.

1802
02:34:06.091 --> 02:34:07.760
I got ready and went.

1803
02:34:07.801 --> 02:34:12.598
From the day I saw the movie.
the shark nightmares were gone.

1804
02:34:13.599 --> 02:34:15.517
Here's the coincidence.

1805
02:34:15.559 --> 02:34:17.227
Guess where I saw the movie.

1806
02:34:17.269 --> 02:34:19.897
I don't know any local cinemas.

1807
02:34:19.938 --> 02:34:21.231
Right here.

1808
02:34:22.525 --> 02:34:24.068
This used to be a cinema?

1809
02:34:24.109 --> 02:34:27.863
The Boa Vista cinema.
where I saw "Jaws".

1810
02:34:28.448 --> 02:34:30.659
- It's changed a lot.
- It has.

1811
02:34:30.700 --> 02:34:32.202
It's a different place.

1812
02:34:32.744 --> 02:34:34.829
And now I work here.

1813
02:34:38.959 --> 02:34:40.710
- Your car?
- It's here.

1814
02:34:41.796 --> 02:34:43.421
Thank you. Fernando.

1815
02:34:43.463 --> 02:34:44.840
Thank you.

1816
